# Global Rules

## User Questions ‚Äî ALWAYS Use `ask` Tool

- NEVER ask questions as plain text in the chat. ALWAYS use the `ask` tool.
- When choosing between approaches ‚Üí `ask` with single-select options (`multi: false`)
- When gathering multiple preferences ‚Üí `ask` with tabbed multi-question interface
- When confirming actions ‚Üí `ask` with Yes/No options
- When you need free-form input ‚Üí `ask` with no options (user types their answer)
- Provide clear, actionable options when available
- Include a `context` field to guide the question

## Markdown

- After creating or writing a markdown file, preview it with `md <file>` in a background job

## CLI Tool Preferences

When using `bash`, prefer modern CLI tools over legacy ones:
- `rg` instead of `grep` (ripgrep ‚Äî faster, respects .gitignore)
- `fd` instead of `find` (fd-find ‚Äî faster, saner defaults)
- `sd` instead of `sed` (simpler syntax, no escaping hell)
- NEVER use `grep`, `find`, or `sed` in bash commands

## Code Style

- Be concise and direct
- Early exit/return patterns, assert preconditions, flat code over nesting
- Conventional Commits format for commit messages
- Explain what you're about to do before doing it
- When making multiple changes, commit frequently with focused messages
- Fish shell, not Zsh or Bash
- Never add comments when removing code
- Don't add explanatory comments unless asked
